# Dashboard.tsx Round 2 patches

Apply these str_replace patches to your mainline Dashboard.tsx. They
add an Open Collection Workbench entry point near the existing Aging
Bucket panel.

## Patch 1 - Add onOpenAging to DashboardProps interface

Find the DashboardProps interface. It should look approximately like:

```typescript
interface DashboardProps {
  lang: Lang;
  result: ParsingPreviewResult | null;
  onBackToUpload: () => void;
  onOpenReview: () => void;
  onOpenReviewCategory: (category: ReviewRoute) => void;
  onOpenParty?: (partyKey: string) => void;
  detailsNotice?: string | null;
}
```

Add a new optional prop, immediately below onOpenParty:

```typescript
  /**
   * v2.3 C2: navigate to /aging when the Open Collection Workbench
   * button is clicked. Follows the existing onOpenReview /
   * onOpenParty callback pattern so Dashboard remains
   * router-agnostic.
   */
  onOpenAging?: () => void;
```

## Patch 2 - Destructure onOpenAging in component signature

Find the destructuring in the Dashboard function declaration:

```typescript
export function Dashboard({
  result,
  onBackToUpload,
  onOpenReview,
  onOpenReviewCategory,
  onOpenParty,
  detailsNotice,
}: DashboardProps) {
```

Add onOpenAging to the destructuring list:

```typescript
export function Dashboard({
  result,
  onBackToUpload,
  onOpenReview,
  onOpenReviewCategory,
  onOpenParty,
  onOpenAging,
  detailsNotice,
}: DashboardProps) {
```

## Patch 3 - Add Open Collection Workbench button

Find the section that renders the Aging Bucket panel. In v2.2 it
typically follows a header like "Aging Buckets" or similar. The
exact wrapping element may be a <section className="aging-buckets">
or similar.

Add a new button block immediately above the aging-buckets section
(so the workbench entry sits at the top of the aging-related area),
OR adjacent to it as a sibling. Either placement satisfies the
Round 2 invariant.

Recommended block:

```tsx
{onOpenAging && (
  <div className="dashboard-workbench-cta">
    <button
      type="button"
      className="btn btn-primary"
      onClick={onOpenAging}
    >
      Open Collection Workbench
    </button>
    <span className="dashboard-workbench-cta-hint">
      Statement Collection Workbench: prioritized view of overdue
      receivables, statement mismatches, and items needing follow-up.
    </span>
  </div>
)}
```

The {onOpenAging && (...)} guard means Dashboard renders cleanly
in environments where the prop is not provided (e.g. legacy tests
or future composition layers).

## Verification

After applying these three patches:

1. Dashboard.tsx compiles without TypeScript errors.
2. The /dashboard route shows an "Open Collection Workbench" button
   (because App.tsx now passes the onOpenAging prop).
3. Clicking the button navigates to /aging.
4. Round 2 invariants:
   `node --experimental-strip-types .\tools\test-aging-report-ui.mjs`
